results.name: Number of permutations of the positive divisors of n, where every element is coprime to its adjacent elements.
comment: Depends only on prime signature; a(A033942(n))=0; a(A037143(n))>0; a(A000430(n))=2; a(A006881(n))=4. - _Reinhard Zumkeller_, May 24 2010
link: R. Zumkeller, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000
formula: a(1)=1, a(p) = 2, a(p^2) = 2, a(p*q) = 4 (where p and q are distinct primes), all other terms are 0.
example: The divisors of 6 are 1, 2, 3 and 6. Of the permutations of these integers, only (6,1,2,3), (6,1,3,2), (2,3,1,6) and (3,2,1,6) are such that every pair of adjacent elements is coprime.
